article.headline: Montana State 57, Howard 54
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Tournament MVP Jason Erickson had 15 points and six assists, helping Montana State beat Howard 57-54 in the championship game of the FIU Tip-Off Classic on Sunday. Matt Towsley and Nick Dissly each scored 11 for Montana State (2-0), which won despite missing half of its 20 free throws. James Wilkinson had game-highs of 21 points, 12 rebounds and five blocked shots for Howard (1-1). Louis Ford and Bilal Russell each scored 10 for the Bison. Neither team shot particularly well; Howard made 39.3 percent of its shots, Montana State shot 38.2 percent. Both teams finished with 37 rebounds. Florida International beat Quinnipiac 66-65 in the tournament's consolation game.
